{{Infobox NFL season | team = Denver Broncos | teamcolor = Denver Broncos 62thru96 | year = 1987 | record = 10â4â1 | division_place = 1st [[AFC West]] | coach = [[Dan Reeves]] | general manager = John Beake | owner = [[Pat Bowlen]] | stadium = [[Mile High Stadium]] | playoffs = Lost [[Super Bowl XXII]] | uniform = }} The '''[[1987 NFL season|1987]] [[Denver Broncos]] season''' was the team's 28th year in professional football and its 18th with the [[National Football League]]. Games scheduled during the third week of the season were cancelled, and games played from weeks 4 to 6 were played with replacement teams. The Broncos finished first in the [[AFC West]], and were AFC Champions for the second straight year. Quarterback [[John Elway]] was voted league [[NFL MVP|MVP]] for 1987.
